                <mxCell id="2" value="&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Object oriented programming concept&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="285" y="-130" width="430" height="420" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="260" y="90" width="400" height="40" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="3" value="Most of the low level programming languages, scalable , multithread programming languages uses OOP" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="2" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="430" height="50" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="15" value="&lt;font face=&quot;Helvetica&quot; style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The term &quot;Object-Oriented&quot; comes from the fundamental concept that this programming paradigm is built around objects as the primary building blocks of software or &quot;objects&quot; as the fundamental building blocks of a program/Software.&lt;/font&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="2" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="80" width="430" height="90" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="136" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Four pillar of OOP: -&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Encapsulation: - By name only we can understand, encapsulating data like attributes and methods within a single unit (the object), and hiding the internal details from outside world&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Abstraction: - hiding the complexity from the end user, and providing easier method for dynamically calculated values, so that user don&#39;t need to calculate&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Polymorphism: - same logic working for different thing in a same way but returns the different dynamic value&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Inheritance: - Means accessing the same properties/methods from another&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="2" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="170" width="430" height="250" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="22" style="edgeStyle=none;html=1;exitX=0;exitY=0.25;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=1;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;flowAnimation=1;" parent="1" source="17" target="107" edge="1">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
                        <mxPoint x="120" y="680" as="targetPoint"/>
                        <mxPoint x="280" y="560" as="sourcePoint"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
