                <mxCell id="17" value="class" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;gradientColor=#7ea6e0;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="330" y="510" width="340" height="90" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="370" y="510" width="70" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="18" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot; face=&quot;-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe WPC, Segoe UI, system-ui, Ubuntu, Droid Sans, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Class is a template/blueprint that is used to create/initialize an instance object&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="17" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="340" height="60" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="26" value="Instance" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="900" y="440" width="335" height="170" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="910" y="460" width="90" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="27" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Instance is a object, return by a class. it structure is alway based on the class blueprint&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;and args of instance depends on the args of class&#39;s constructor&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;and a instance object, will only have the values that has been explicitly added in the instance object via constructor&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="26" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="335" height="140" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="156" style="edgeStyle=none;html=1;exitX=0.75;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=1;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="149" target="153">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="149" value="Inheritance" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="282.5" y="-520" width="435" height="200" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="285" y="-530" width="90" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="150" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;1. By the name only we can undestand that it means we inherit the properties of one class into another class, and this inherited class is called sub-class&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Bydefualt it inherits all the properties of the class&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="149">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="435" height="60" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="152" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2. we can also inherit specific properties from &lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(0, 101, 255));&quot;&gt;parent class constructor (called super constructor)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(#ffffff, var(--ge-dark-color, #121212));&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Even when we inherit specific properties from super constructor all the properties will be inherited with their defualt values if assigned else falsy value or forced to initialized non-inherited property in the super constructor in some langauge&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="149">
                    <mxGeometry y="90" width="435" height="110" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
