                <mxCell id="33" value="variables" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;gradientColor=#97d077;strokeColor=#82b366;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="-35" y="1250" width="300" height="300" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-35" y="1350" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="135" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Variables declaration and initialization in class: -&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;In Dynamic language, Variable declaration is not needed but in static language field declaration is needed even for constructor args. (to know reason refer &lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(204, 0, 204));&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ce.svg&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;In Dynamic language, Bydefault Variable initialization is undefined, while in most static language string = null, integer = 0 and boolean = false, object reference = null. In some languages explicit initialization may also be needed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="33" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="300" height="190" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="36" value="1. Class variables" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="33" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="220" width="300" height="40" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="37" value="2. Instance only variables" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="33" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="260" width="300" height="40" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="121" value="Nested Class" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;gradientColor=#97d077;strokeColor=#82b366;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="360" y="1270" width="300" height="70" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-35" y="1350" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="122" value="1.&amp;nbsp;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="121" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="300" height="40" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="79" value="Accessibility of properties" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="50" y="2480" width="390" height="340" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-35" y="1350" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="80" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Within the Class, In both the cases, static and non-static property, and whether&amp;nbsp; property is public or private: -&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;A class method can only access class properties&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;but Instance method can access both class and instance properties&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="79" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="390" height="130" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="132" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;In both the cases, static and non-static, private property cannot be accessed outside the class&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;but public property can be accessed in both within and outside of the class&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Static properties can only be accessed using class name itself withing and outside of the class&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;And Instance properties can only be accessed using that specific instance name only, and using &quot;this&quot; keyword within the class&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="79" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="160" width="390" height="180" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="92" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(72, 72, 72), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Access Modifiers&lt;/font&gt;" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="50" y="2060" width="390" height="310" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="300" y="1575" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="93" value="1. Public: -&amp;nbsp; bydefualt all properties(static and non-static) are public, which mean properties can be accessed outside of the class" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="92" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="390" height="60" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="94" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2. Private: - When we don&#39;t the any properties to be accessible outside of the class, we can make that property private&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;When we have some variable or methods that only required within the classs for internal purpose only, then in this case we can make those properties private&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="92" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="90" width="390" height="120" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="139" value="3. Protected: - When we want the property to accessible only within the class, and within is sub-classes but not from outside of the class" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="92" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="210" width="390" height="50" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="144" value="etc... there are more access modifier in static languages" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="92">
                    <mxGeometry y="260" width="390" height="50" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
