                <mxCell id="23" value="Constructor types" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;gradientColor=#ea6b66;strokeColor=#b85450;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="-810" y="210" width="400" height="300" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-740" y="240" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="24" value="1. public constructor: - This is defualt constructor type, mean we can create instance using that class" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="23" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="400" height="40" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="114" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2.private contructor: -&amp;nbsp; Menas n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe WPC&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, system-ui, Ubuntu, &amp;quot;Droid Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;o one outside the class can create/initialize instance objects directly using that class. Only the class itself can create its instance&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;When our code within the class is like this that we don&#39;t need to create any instance from that class, the we can make that class constructor a private constructor&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Like when all the properties in our class are static&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;when we have anonymous static method with will be executed as soon as the class object is registered,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Incase of singleton pattern&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="23" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="70" width="400" height="200" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="52" value="3. Multiple constructor: -" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="23" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="270" width="400" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="107" value="Constructor" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;gradientColor=#ea6b66;strokeColor=#b85450;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="-200" y="395" width="370" height="270" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-210" y="465" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="108" value="1. Constructor: - by the name only we can understand that the it constructs the structure of the instance, So it serves as the initialization mechanism fro instance object, setting up their&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(0, 101, 255));&quot;&gt; initial state/values&lt;/span&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="107" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="370" height="80" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="117" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2. Default constructor in most of the programming language is No-arg constructor.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Constructor don&#39;t have any return type, because they implicity return the newly created object&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="107" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="110" width="370" height="70" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="113" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;3. This constructor funciton alway runs, when we initialized/create any instance.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;So we can also defined some code logic in constructor that we want to perfrom before any instance initialization&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="107" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="180" width="370" height="90" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="125" style="edgeStyle=none;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;flowAnimation=1;" parent="1" source="55" target="121" edge="1">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="55" value="Properties of class" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;gradientColor=#97d077;strokeColor=#82b366;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="320" y="750" width="370" height="360" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="315" y="960" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="56" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;In class architecture, we need to thing&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;We&amp;nbsp; want some properties to be same everywhere (same in memory), so to access these properties we have to obviously use the class name itselt&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;and some properties to be specific to each instance (unique memory for each instance), accessed via instance name&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(192, 192, 192);&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(192, 192, 192), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;this is where the concept of static and no&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(192, 192, 192);&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(192, 192, 192), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;n-static comes in&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="55" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="370" height="150" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="61" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;static properties means &lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(0, 101, 255));&quot;&gt;class properties/members&lt;/span&gt; which will be same everywhere,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;non-static properties are specific to each instance, thatswhy these are called &lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(0, 101, 255));&quot;&gt;instance properties/members&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="55" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="180" width="370" height="80" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="43" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;So class method receives the class object itself, thatswhy this keyword in class method points to class object itself&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;and instance method receives the instance object, thatswhy this keyword in instance method points to instance object itselt&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="55" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="260" width="370" height="100" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="29" value="in js" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1600" y="1575" width="390" height="130" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-170" y="710" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="30" value="class is constructor funciton" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="29" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="390" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="31" value="so the args of this function are passed in constructor of the class&lt;div&gt;and to add the args in the newly created instance object, we have obviously assign it&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="29" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="60" width="390" height="70" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="102" value="constructor args" style="swimlane;fontStyle=0;childLayout=stackLayout;horizontal=1;startSize=30;horizontalStack=0;resizeParent=1;resizeParentMax=0;resizeLast=0;collapsible=1;marginBottom=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;gradientColor=#ea6b66;strokeColor=#b85450;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="-815" y="690" width="410" height="140" as="geometry">
                        <mxRectangle x="-170" y="710" width="130" height="30" as="alternateBounds"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="66" value="1. Dynamic field: - the constructor args are the dynamic values, that we want creating a instance" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="102" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="410" height="40" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="105" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2. And we have to explicitly add these constructor args to the instance object, if we want to access them via instance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;we can also add any value that is not in arg with any value&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="102" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="70" width="410" height="70" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="84" style="edgeStyle=none;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;flowAnimation=1;" parent="1" source="92" target="79" edge="1">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
                        <mxPoint x="-130" y="2385" as="targetPoint"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
